00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,880
It has been confirmed

2
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:50,360
that the skeleton found by the villagers a few days ago

3
00:01:50,560 --> 00:01:53,600
belongs to Mr. Jiang's daughter, who went missing eight years ago.

4
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,120
Moreover, Mr. Jiang

5
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:57,020
has also identified the remains.

6
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:57,960
This way.

7
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,360
Okay.

8
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,280
We have reached the skeleton.

9
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:04,640
Go a bit further.

10
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,040
Look.

11
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,039
I forgot you can't see.

12
00:02:11,039 --> 00:02:13,080
But I noticed something strange.

13
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:17,040
There are pieces of red cloth on her upper body.

14
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,440
But Mr. Jiang told me

15
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:22,960
that his daughter didn't own a red dress.

16
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,450
Could it have been left by the culprit?

17
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,840
The young lady wanted to keep this boy,

18
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,120
bought him a house,

19
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,400
and had him repay the debt by solving cases.

20
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:37,300
He gets two taels of silver for every case he solves.

21
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,560
But she forgot

22
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:42,200
that Jueming can't stand the sight of corpses at all.

23
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,600
Then deduct one tael of silver from his pay.

24
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,760
His martial arts aren't as good as mine either.

25
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:49,680
Indeed.

26
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,600
My son is so amazing.

27
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,700
Let's deduct another tael of silver.

28
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
I think it's still a girl.

29
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,840
Let me untie you first.

30
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,079
Hey.

31
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,520
Don't look this way.

32
00:03:22,040 --> 00:03:23,079
Wait a moment.

33
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:26,960
Usually, only corpses come here.

34
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:29,240
Very few living people do.

35
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,560
Um, let me find it.

36
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,480
This one.

37
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:37,960
Here, look.

38
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:45,240
And this is the statement.

39
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,530
Mr. Jiang's statement.

40
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,160
Yes.

41
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,850
From a single skeleton,

42
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:59,480
you can vividly describe the victim's murder.

43
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,680
That's truly rare.

44
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,480
As a woman,

45
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,330
why would you choose to deal with corpses?

46
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,420
You don't have to tell me if you don't want to.

47
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:23,160
I grew up without a mother,

48
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,480
and my father was rarely home.

49
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:29,320
I watched the small animals I raised slowly die,

50
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:32,280
so I got used to dead bodies.

51
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,120
Later, I started studying them.

52
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,960
I studied why they died

53
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,240
and why they got sick.

54
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:41,880
Then, I secretly watched my father judge cases,

55
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:44,520
and read a lot of coroners' documents.

56
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:48,960
I found that the dead are more honest than the living.

57
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,000
Corpses don't lie.

58
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,240
They just lie there quietly.

59
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,380
As long as you are careful enough,

60
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:01,480
you can definitely find the stories they carry.

61
00:05:02,680 --> 00:05:05,120
What you say makes some sense.

62
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,280
Others work as coroners for a living.

63
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:11,120
You do it out of true passion.

64
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:15,600
And it saves me a lot of trouble.

65
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,960
As the daughter of the Deputy Prefect,

66
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,880
what trouble could you possibly have?

67
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,680
Of course I have a lot of trouble.

68
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:27,400
This is the son of Zhao Qi, the Vice Minister of Revenue,

69
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,560
Young Master Zhao.

70
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:33,040
This is my daughter, Li Jinglan.

71
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:35,640
You two are of a similar age.

72
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:39,159
You must have a lot to talk about.

73
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,560
Young Master Zhao, please have a seat.

74
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,320
Have a seat.

75
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:50,560
I heard from Lord Li that you also like reading.

76
00:05:51,040 --> 00:05:54,100
I wonder if it's "The Analects" or "The Five Classics"?

77
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,080
Neither.

78
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:57,960
I like reading the Huangdi Neijing

79
00:05:58,080 --> 00:05:59,920
and Tanglu Shilu.

80
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:00,880
It talks about

81
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,940
various structures of the human body

82
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,760
and the tragic states of different deceased.

83
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,800
From the perspective of a corpse,

84
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,680
first of all,

85
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,010
it is very interesting.

86
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:17,560
You must know how to embroider.

87
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:20,400
Embroidery?

88
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,840
It's a bit tedious.

89
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,840
However, I am good at suturing corpses.

90
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,560
It's okay. Never mind.

91
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:29,200
My daughter is just getting carried away.

92
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,400
Mr. Zhao, please don't mind her.

93
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:36,159
May I ask why you always deal with corpses?

94
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,720
Because I am a coroner.

95
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:40,040
To me,

96
00:06:40,080 --> 00:06:41,800
corpses can talk.

97
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:44,130
Whether it's a headless corpse

98
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,560
or various dismembered body parts,

99
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:49,360
I can touch them with both hands

100
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:51,360
and carefully examine them.

101
00:06:54,320 --> 00:06:55,480
I suddenly remembered.

102
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,800
My father has an appointment.

103
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,200
I have other things to do.

104
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:00,320
Goodbye.

105
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,000
Take care, Mr. Zhao.

106
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:03,680
Mr. Zhao!

107
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,280
Mr. Zhao!

108
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,520
My daughter,

109
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,360
if you keep fooling around like this,

110
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,680
who will dare to marry you?

111
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,280
I'm just telling the truth.

112
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,090
Without blind dates

113
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,960
and the etiquette of a lady,

114
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,400
you will find that getting along with corpses

115
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,080
is much more peaceful.

116
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,860
How did you know I am the daughter of the Deputy Magistrate?

117
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,400
You can walk safely in front

118
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,640
and let Constable Su walk behind you.

119
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,480
You are no ordinary coroner.

120
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:39,960
In this Luoyang City,

121
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,680
although the magistrate is respected,

122
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:44,000
the people who can make his constables obey them completely

123
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,080
are very few.

124
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,200
The magistrate only has one son,

125
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,600
who is still a child.

126
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,040
The wealthy merchants in the city

127
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,080
are rich,

128
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,020
but they can only maneuver in business matters.

129
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,600
Although there are high officials and nobles,

130
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,159
they serve their own masters

131
00:07:57,159 --> 00:08:00,000
and are not closely related to the affairs of the yamen.

132
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,320
Taking everything into account,

133
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:02,380
your surname is Li,

134
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:06,000
you must be the only daughter of Deputy Magistrate Li Ze,

135
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,920
Li Jinglan.

136
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:12,240
This guy really has some skills.

137
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,360
I think he just got lucky.

138
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,840
I read Lord Jiang's confession.

139
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,240
Jiang Siyan left the candy shop that day

140
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,160
and headed home.

141
00:08:22,640 --> 00:08:25,200
If we walk her route home,

142
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,480
we should be able to find some clues.

143
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,960
This case happened eight years ago.

144
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:33,419
What clues could there be?

145
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:41,400
Jiang Siyan took this road home that day.

146
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,400
There are so many people on this street.

147
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,120
The crime couldn't have been committed here.

148
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,440
Come, take a look!

149
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:54,800
Candied hawthorns! Fresh candied hawthorns! Take a look!

150
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,400
Delicious wontons!

151
00:08:57,800 --> 00:09:00,040
Fresh out of the pot! It smells great!

152
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,600
Official trinkets!

153
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,720
Come and take a look!

154
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,520
Candied hawthorns!

155
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,480
My silk is the best!

156
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:10,480
Wait.

157
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:13,640
That day,

158
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:17,320
Mr. Jiang found the little girl's embroidered shoe right here.

159
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,600
There are very few pedestrians here.

160
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,400
And Jiang Siyan might have come home at night.

161
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,760
If it was night,

162
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,760
and if it was raining,

163
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,810
it would be easier to commit the crime.

164
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:58,410
Who knows which shop sells this yellow paper?

165
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,080
You don't think

166
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,930
the killer came to burn this in person, do you?

167
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,200
After committing their first murder, many suspects,

168
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,730
even if they aren't caught,

169
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,040
at certain times,

170
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:12,400
will restlessly return to the scene.

171
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,240
They either watch silently,

172
00:11:15,520 --> 00:11:16,120
or

173
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:17,920
burn some yellow paper,

174
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:20,800
praying not to be haunted by vengeful spirits.

175
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:22,320
Honestly,

176
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,380
what he said makes some sense.

177
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,250
I've also heard that

178
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,840
if a person dies an unjust death,

179
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:31,000
and their grievances are not redressed,

180
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,130
they won't be willing to reincarnate.

181
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:33,880
Their soul

182
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:37,360
will repeatedly wander around the place they were murdered.

183
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:42,850
You saying this yellow paper was burned by the killer

184
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,120
is quite possible.

185
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,120
These are all businesses here,

186
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,250
with no residences.

187
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:51,600
Really, coming here to burn paper is very suspicious.

188
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:57,640
If this yellow paper was really burned by the suspect,

189
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,600
then this is our only hope.

190
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:04,210
This talisman looks like it was drawn by Daoist Priest Chen,

191
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:05,240
right?

192
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:08,480
Look.

193
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,200
Was this bought from you?

194
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:23,360
This was indeed bought from me.

195
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:26,640
I even drew the disaster-averting talisman on it myself.

196
00:12:26,640 --> 00:12:28,520
Do you remember who bought it?

197
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:34,840
During the Ghost Festival, there are too many people buying this kind of paper.

198
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:38,180
But not many ask for this disaster-averting talisman.

199
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,040
Then recently,

200
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,080
who bought a lot of it?

201
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,720
Let me think.

202
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,600
Let me remind you.

203
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:49,560
Has anyone recently said

204
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:52,160
they felt like they did something guilty

205
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,330
and couldn't sleep?

206
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:56,160
Guilty?

207
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,080
I remember now.

208
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,760
There's a man named Cao Tai.

209
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:03,420
He said he did something wrong

210
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,480
and couldn't sleep well at night.

211
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,840
He said he always felt like his house was haunted at night,

212
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,890
and specifically asked me to do a ritual at his house.

213
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:19,800
I know I was wrong.

214
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,920
He said he did something wrong

215
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,360
and was haunted by vengeful spirits.

216
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:26,680
Didn't you ask him what he did wrong?

217
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:30,280
You know, I'm just a talisman seller.

218
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:31,960
Every day,

219
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,800
those who come to pray for blessings or confess

220
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,400
are everywhere.

221
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,480
I can't ask everything.

222
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:41,760
I wouldn't have time to ask them all.

223
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,600
Besides,

224
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:46,440
who hasn't done something they feel guilty about?

225
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:47,960
Put simply,

226
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:51,480
don't you have any secrets?

227
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:53,720
This Cao Tai...

228
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,080
Let's go. Take us to his house.

229
00:13:56,960 --> 00:13:58,290
This is Cao Tai's house.

230
00:13:58,760 --> 00:13:59,320
Cao Tai!

231
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:00,880
Cao Tai!

232
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,280
What is this stuff?

233
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:03,800
Did you do this?

234
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:05,080
Cao Tai told me to do it.

235
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:07,180
I'm just trying to make a living here.

236
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,360
Cao Tai.

237
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,080
Hurry, come here.

238
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:15,120
Come.

239
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:15,560
Here.

240
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,820
Hurry and let him down.

241
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:22,920
How did he die?

242
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:25,000
Are you okay?

243
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:25,960
I'm fine.

244
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:27,320
How did he die?

245
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:28,960
I'll go check.

246
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:34,730
Put him down.

247
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:45,400
There are no obvious signs of a struggle on the body.

248
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:53,690
The strangulation mark on the neck is clear and obvious.

249
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:55,560
Aside from the strangulation mark,

250
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,490
there are no obvious injuries on the rest of the body.

251
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:01,720
Judging from the stiffness of the knuckles

252
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,440
and the ambient temperature,

253
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:07,650
the victim probably died last night during the You hour.

254
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:12,090
Are there any other items near him?

255
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,600
There's only a wooden ladder.

256
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,520
It must have been used for the hanging.

257
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,240
Do not move any items.

258
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,160
Move this away first.

259
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:22,040
Alright,

260
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,880
you guys, come

261
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,320
carry the body away first.

262
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,200
Hurry.

263
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,240
Can I go now?

264
00:15:34,440 --> 00:15:36,500
When did he buy the talisman from you?

265
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:39,600
Yesterday, around the Shen hour.

266
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,360
This has nothing to do with me.

267
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,640
I just sell talismans.

268
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:44,520
You can't go yet.

269
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:48,000
You'll come back to the yamen with us later for questioning.

270
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,160
Stay right here.

271
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:50,780
Alright, next,

272
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:53,680
let's have our master step up.

273
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,880
The rope's structure is intact.

274
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,810
The angle and position are normal.

275
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,880
It looks like a typical hanging.

276
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:14,760
Combined with the autopsy results,

277
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:16,520
it is indeed a suicide by hanging.

278
00:16:16,520 --> 00:16:18,120
The body has been moved away.

279
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,880
If he can really find something out,

280
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:20,960
I'll be damned.

281
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,420
What are you doing?

282
00:16:27,280 --> 00:16:29,120
Imitating the victim's actions before death.

283
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,320
You're doing this again?

284
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,320
Doing what again?

285
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,480
When I first met him,

286
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,580
he was in a coffin imitating a corpse.

287
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,800
Imitating a corpse?

288
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,560
It seems he forgot to tell us

289
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,200
when to let him down.

290
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,880
Is he... is he dying?

291
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:54,800
No.

292
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:57,000
If he really can't take it, he'll tell us.

293
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,000
Right.

294
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:09,200
He probably can't take it anymore.

295
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,599
Hurry, let him down.

296
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,440
Can't take it?

297
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:14,640
Danger!

298
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:16,960
Hurry!

299
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,260
It's been a long time since I made such an error in judgment.

300
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:23,920
Drink some water.

301
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:26,920
Kid, were you really suffocating?

302
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:30,560
That ladder,

303
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:32,240
has it been moved?

304
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:33,480
No.

305
00:17:33,840 --> 00:17:35,040
It hasn't been moved.

306
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,840
If that's the case,

307
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,720
there must have been another person in this room.

308
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,600
Normally, when a person hangs themselves,

309
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,360
they step on a chair. After the chair falls,

310
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,240
their legs dangle and struggle.

311
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,640
The body will instinctively try desperately to save itself.

312
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,120
At this point, if they were given a solid object,

313
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,440
they absolutely wouldn't die.

314
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,240
Unless...

315
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:02,620
Unless someone grabbed him tightly,

316
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,340
preventing him from stepping on the ladder.

317
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:12,360
What is this?

318
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:13,740
Bring it here quickly.

319
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,760
Are there any women in Cao's family?

320
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:29,080
I... I really don't know.

321
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,440
You are useless.

322
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:31,920
This Cao Tai,

323
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:33,420
is he some kind of pervert?

324
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:38,980
This blindfold isn't bad, right?

325
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,160
I made it.

326
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:46,740
The young lady is indeed beautiful and intelligent. A true lady from a noble family.

327
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:03,450
Smelling the corpse blindfolded.

328
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,800
There's a strong smell of rouge on his legs,

329
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,840
mixed with a herbal scent.

330
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,160
There are no herbs kept in his house.

331
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,280
The suspect

332
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:22,960
is very likely a woman,

333
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:25,370
and has something to do with herbs.

334
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:34,480
Could it be that the suspect has a sick patient at home?

335
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:37,240
Judging from this smell,

336
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:41,240
it's more like someone who deals with medicinal materials all year round.

337
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,480
Only they would have such a strong herbal smell on them.

338
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:44,240
Perhaps

339
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,370
it's related to a pharmacy.

340
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:47,780
Captain Su,

341
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:51,520
immediately search all the pharmacies Cao Tai visited when he was alive,

342
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,250
starting from when he was born.

343
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:54,680
I'll get to it right away.

344
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:56,120
I've checked.

345
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:58,040
Among the dozens of pharmacies in Luoyang,

346
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,800
this is the only one with a female shopkeeper

347
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,600
and associated with Cao Tai at the same time.

348
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:05,720
And this place is only a mile away from Cao Tai's house.

349
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:06,720
Right here.

350
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:07,760
So it's this one.

351
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,480
Look at the paper umbrellas.

352
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:10,610
Come and take a look.

353
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,800
This pharmacy belongs to my husband.

354
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,650
Unfortunately, today,

355
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:30,320
he went up the mountain to gather herbs,

356
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,720
and hasn't returned yet.

357
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,200
Didn't it rain heavily yesterday?

358
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,400
So I closed the shop early

359
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,360
and never left the house.

360
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,560
So you were home alone last night?

361
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:45,640
Captain Su, you might as well speak frankly.

362
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:51,320
Last night, Cao Tai died in his home.

363
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Don't be nervous.

364
00:20:54,440 --> 00:20:55,880
In order to solve the case,

365
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:59,160
we are questioning everyone he knew one by one.

366
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,280
He died?

367
00:21:02,760 --> 00:21:03,800
How did he die?

368
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:07,640
Could it really be that his life was claimed by a ghost?

369
00:21:07,640 --> 00:21:09,840
Mrs. Wang, what do you mean by that?

370
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:12,080
Did Cao Tai say something to you?

371
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:14,680
Come, sit down, tell us slowly.

372
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:18,360
Cao Tai often came here to get medicine.

373
00:21:18,560 --> 00:21:20,880
We got familiar with each other over time.

374
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:23,120
Yesterday afternoon, he came to see me.

375
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:29,330
You're here.

376
00:21:29,720 --> 00:21:31,520
What medicine do you need today?

377
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:34,080
What's wrong?

378
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:38,360
I want some medicine to calm the nerves.

379
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,240
What happened?

380
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:46,580
I did something wrong.

381
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,400
A ghost is trying to take my life.

382
00:21:48,400 --> 00:21:49,680
Please,

383
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:50,720
save me.

384
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,280
Okay.

385
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,680
Save me.

386
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,460
I asked him what was wrong,

387
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,850
but he wouldn't tell me.

388
00:22:00,120 --> 00:22:00,800
In the end,

389
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,370
he left in a daze by himself,

390
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,660
and even forgot to take his medicine.

391
00:22:13,280 --> 00:22:16,040
Constable Su, this is the medicine Cao Tai prescribed.

392
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,000
Now, he can't take it anymore.

393
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:24,880
Su Lang.

394
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,300
Where is my father?

395
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:32,960
He went to gather herbs

396
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,280
and will be back tomorrow.

397
00:22:34,280 --> 00:22:36,040
Then please give him a message when he returns.

398
00:22:36,040 --> 00:22:37,770
Tell him I came looking for him.

399
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,090
Never mind, don't look for him.

400
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,000
I'll tell him myself.

401
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:45,440
Okay.

402
00:22:46,960 --> 00:22:48,290
Who is this little girl?

403
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:51,400
My husband's child with his ex-wife.

404
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:56,800
I want to ask,

405
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:57,960
did Mrs. Wang

406
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,000
meet anyone in the shop yesterday?

407
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,080
Well,

408
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:01,800
no.

409
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,960
Did the proprietress of Baicao Hall go out yesterday?

410
00:23:04,960 --> 00:23:06,160
It rained at 5 PM yesterday.

411
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:07,280
I went back early.

412
00:23:07,320 --> 00:23:08,580
I didn't see anything.

413
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:11,480
Excuse me, did you see the proprietress of this shop go out yesterday?

414
00:23:11,480 --> 00:23:13,080
Thank you, sir. I don't know.

415
00:23:16,040 --> 00:23:17,770
Did Mrs. Wang go out yesterday?

416
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,330
I don't know.

417
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:23,000
I don't know. I didn't pay attention. Okay, thank you. Okay.

418
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,440
Brother, did Mrs. Wang go out yesterday?

419
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:26,770
I don't know.

420
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:29,140
I found out something.

421
00:23:29,520 --> 00:23:30,720
At 1 PM yesterday,

422
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:32,440
Cao Tai did come to see Mrs. Wang,

423
00:23:32,440 --> 00:23:34,840
and they stayed together for about an hour.

424
00:23:34,840 --> 00:23:38,280
After that, Cao Tai probably went to see Taoist Chen.

425
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:39,840
What about 5 PM yesterday?

426
00:23:39,840 --> 00:23:41,160
It was raining heavily.

427
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,690
People all stayed indoors.

428
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,280
There was no one on the street.

429
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:46,880
So no one noticed if she went out.

430
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:49,720
That woman we just met,

431
00:23:49,960 --> 00:23:51,320
bring her to the government office.

432
00:23:51,320 --> 00:23:53,720
We should be able to get something from her.

433
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:05,660
How many days have you been starving?

434
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,720
I only came because you said I could eat my fill.

435
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:13,080
I mean, eat slowly.

436
00:24:18,680 --> 00:24:20,120
What do you want to ask?

437
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:21,940
I'll answer while eating.

438
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:28,240
You don't seem to like your father's new wife.

439
00:24:29,320 --> 00:24:30,640
Would you like her if you were me?

440
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,300
I'm not afraid to let you know.

441
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:34,640
This Baicao Hall was built by my birth parents,

442
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:37,300
step by step, from a street stall to a small shop.

443
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:40,540
She, on the other hand, seduced my father with her wiles

444
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:41,890
and got a high position.

445
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:45,300
It seems your father isn't a good person either.

446
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:47,480
That's right.

447
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:51,640
So now, I don't have much contact with them.

448
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:54,400
If my mother hadn't told me to fulfill my filial piety,

449
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:57,200
I definitely wouldn't have any contact with them.

450
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,160
Then you used to live with your father.

451
00:24:59,160 --> 00:25:01,490
Why did you move in with your mother later?

452
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:04,200
Because she thinks

453
00:25:04,720 --> 00:25:07,650
I'm the reason she can never have a child in this life.

454
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:14,360
At that time, she was pregnant

455
00:25:15,360 --> 00:25:18,020
and was in charge of decocting medicine at home.

456
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:38,440
What happened?

457
00:25:39,280 --> 00:25:40,760
Madam.

458
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:43,560
Madam.

459
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:46,280
Madam,

460
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:47,200
wait a moment.

461
00:25:47,240 --> 00:25:48,240
I'll go get your medicine.

462
00:25:48,240 --> 00:25:49,170
Don't be afraid.

463
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,000
Our child will be fine.

464
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:53,370
Don't be afraid.

465
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:59,170
After this fall, she will never be able to have children.

466
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:01,840
Tell me, is this retribution?

467
00:26:03,760 --> 00:26:05,220
Was she careless herself,

468
00:26:05,720 --> 00:26:07,050
or did you push her down?

469
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:12,160
My father asked me the same thing back then.

470
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,000
What do you think?

471
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:29,880
I asked Lord Jiang.

472
00:26:30,720 --> 00:26:32,640
Lord Jiang said this handkerchief is not theirs.

473
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,770
Jiang Siyan doesn't know them either.

474
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,720
There is no bad blood between their two families.

475
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,980
Jiang Siyan doesn't know Cao Tai either.

476
00:26:40,280 --> 00:26:42,880
There is no grudge between their two families.

477
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:47,580
This handkerchief

478
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:49,600
is mine.

479
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:51,720
It's yours?

480
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:01,320
I want it. Give it to me.

481
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:02,560
So sweet.

482
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:04,800
So delicious.

483
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,480
Your handkerchief is so pretty.

484
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,440
It's for you.

485
00:27:07,480 --> 00:27:08,200
Thank you.

486
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,160
Your home is far.

487
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,380
Take the umbrella.

488
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:18,080
No need.

489
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:20,320
My family might come to pick me up later.

490
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:22,280
Didn't your father go to gather herbs?

491
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:24,800
Your father's new wife definitely won't come to pick you up.

492
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:25,720
Just take it.

493
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:26,690
Don't be polite.

494
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:27,720
Thank you.

495
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,280
Come.

496
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:33,400
Put this coat on.

497
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:34,600
No need.

498
00:27:34,920 --> 00:27:36,440
It's cold outside. Don't catch a cold.

499
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,160
Okay.

500
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:40,520
Thank you.

501
00:27:41,360 --> 00:27:42,290
I'm leaving now.

502
00:27:42,760 --> 00:27:44,440
Goodbye.

503
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,330
It rained heavily that day.

504
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:53,010
She handed me the umbrella.

505
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:56,000
So I took off my coat and put it on her.

506
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:59,320
When she left, she clearly took this handkerchief with her.

507
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:02,760
But now, why would it appear in the shrine?

508
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:07,640
Right.

509
00:28:08,920 --> 00:28:10,050
Where are you going?

510
00:28:10,360 --> 00:28:10,960
Cao Tai.

511
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:12,240
To Cao Tai's house.

512
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:12,900
Wait for me.

513
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:13,880
I'll go with you.

514
00:28:14,720 --> 00:28:15,360
Okay.

515
00:28:15,760 --> 00:28:18,040
You two slow down.

516
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:18,720
Okay.

517
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:21,240
Let her pack the chicken to go.

518
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:25,000
Slow down, girl.

519
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:25,960
Don't choke.

520
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:29,530
It's all yours. No one is fighting with you for it.

521
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:34,280
Like this.

522
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:35,320
You go out now.

523
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:36,640
I am Cao Tai, you are the female ghost.

524
00:28:36,640 --> 00:28:37,560
You go out and come in again.

525
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:38,120
Okay.

526
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:38,720
Okay.

527
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:06,920
I know the murderer's modus operandi.

